The API uses the  jsend  standard for JSON responses.  This responses are possible:  Success message:  {
    status : "success",
    message : "This is a success message"
}  Success (single object):  {
    status : "success",
    data : {
        "post" : { "id" : 1, "title" : "A blog post", "body" : "Some useful content" }
     }
}  Success (multiple objects):  {
    status : "success",
    data : {
        "posts" : [
            { "id" : 1, "title" : "A blog post", "body" : "Some useful content" },
            { "id" : 2, "title" : "Another blog post", "body" : "More content" },
        ]
     }
}  Error message:  {
    status : "error",
    message : "This is a error message"
}

The ping resource can be used to check the api health.  Request:  GET /ping  Response:  {
    "status": "success",
    "message": "All systems operate as expected."
}

The user resource gives you information about your user profile.  Request:  GET /user?access_token=<access_token>  Response:  {
   "status":"success",
   "data":{
      "user":{
         "user_id":1337,
         "username":"Marty",
         "timezone":"America/Los_Angeles",
         "email":"marty.mcfly@biffco.com",
         "credit":1955,
         "currency":"EUR",
         "registred":"1985-25-10T01:15:00.000+00:00",
         "language":"eng",
         "avatar":"https://server.nitrado.net/users.nitrado/1337.jpg",
         "profile":{
            "name":"Marty McFly",
            "street":"DeLorean Street 12",
            "postcode":"2209",
            "city":"Hill Valley"
         }
      }
   }
}

To access the webinterface you need a special access token with a lifetime of 24 hours.
You can request this access token via this endpoint.  The token will only change every 24 hours and will be cached.
For detailed information about the Webinterface Login please  click here .  Request:  GET /user/webinterface_token?access_token=<access_token>  Response:  {
   "status":"success",
   "data":{
      "token":{
         "token":"mRtAApJS2XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXw6scyt9g7CsKAfg0MpjMQ5PfXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXW",
         "valid_until":"2016-01-22T14:01:03"
      }
   }
}

This endpoint allows you to logout all users from your webinterface.  Request:  DELETE /user/webinterface_token?access_token=<access_token>  Response:  {
   "status":"success",
   "message":"All webinterface tokens has been expired from the system."
}

